HEADWORD: Spattling-poppy
<hw>Spat"tling-pop"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>spattle</ets> to spit + E. <ets>poppy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of catchfly (<spn>Silene inflata</spn>)
which is sometimes frothy from the action of captured insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spatula</ent>⟦br⟧
